<subSubSection id="C3746542FFC6FF9CFF38F9AA1D937310" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="251" pageId="3" pageNumber="250" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD136C9FFC6FF9BFF38F9AA1D2B7373" blockId="3.[151,1437,1589,2012]" box="[151,317,1589,1615]" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">
<heading id="D09981A5FFC6FF9BFF38F9AA1D2B7373" bold="true" box="[151,317,1589,1615]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="250" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B91AEADBFFC6FF9BFF38F9AA1D2B7373" bold="true" box="[151,317,1589,1615]" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">Redescription</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136C9FFC6FF9CFF38F9C61D78747D" blockId="3.[151,1437,1589,2012]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,753]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="251" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">
<emphasis id="B91AEADBFFC6FF9BFF38F9C61CE5734F" box="[151,243,1625,1651]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">Female.</emphasis>
Length, 2.0 mm. Body dark brown to black; head with bluish shine, face above with a violet cross-band; inter-torular area up to mouth margin purple; malar space bluish in upper half, violet in lower half. Antenna with scape and pedicel dark brown; F1–4 yellow, F1 with slightly pale brown infuscation basally (in cleared and slidemounted antenna, F1–4 appear white); clava with first and third segments pale brown, second segment brownish yellow. Mesosoma with pronotum with bluish shine; mesoscutum purple, anteriorly and laterally with some greenish shine, but in some lights appears largely greenish blue; axillae dull bronzy with bluish green shine; scutellum mainly purple, with sides and apex bluish; tegula dark brown; metanotum and propodeum black; prepectus purple, posteriorly white; mesopleuron dark brown. Fore wing with hyaline and infuscated areas as in 
<figureCitation id="13552A4CFFC6FF9BFB7EF8CA19017253" box="[1233,1303,1877,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 1, 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1412,1436]" captionTargetBox="[156,1413,790,1374]" captionTargetId="figure-297@4.[156,1431,774,1385]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1, 2. Caenohomalopoda albifuniculata Hayat, holotype, female. 1, antenna; 2, fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524430/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
. Hind wing hyaline. Fore leg: coxa dark brown in basal half, white in apical half; trochanter white; femur yellow with a pale brown streak along ventral margin; tibia yellow with a narrow brown streak along ventral margin, tarsus brownish yellow. Mid leg: coxa dark brown; trochanter brownish yellow; femur brownish yellow with a dark brown streak along ventral margin (one-third the width of femur); tibia white with a brown streak in basal half of ventral margin; spur and tarsal segments 1–4 white, 5th segment pale brown. Hind leg: coxa nearly black; trochanter pale brown, femur black except base narrowly pale brown; tibia black except white apical fifth; tarsal segments 1–4 white, 5th brown. Gaster with T1 bluish, other tergites dark brown with at most dark violet shine; exserted part of ovipositor sheath dark brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136C9FFC1FF9CFF68FED41D3274C9" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">
Head. Frontovertex width 0.3× head width; posterior ocellus very close to eye margin; POL slightly less than OCL (7.5:8); frontovertex with raised reticulate sculpture, setae small and silvery white, those on upper part of occiput brown [The pair of long, scale-like setae at vertexo-occipital margin lost]. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13552A4CFFC1FF9CFB66FE0C191B7491" box="[1225,1293,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1, 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1412,1436]" captionTargetBox="[156,1413,790,1374]" captionTargetId="figure-297@4.[156,1431,774,1385]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1, 2. Caenohomalopoda albifuniculata Hayat, holotype, female. 1, antenna; 2, fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524430/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) with scape 4.15× as long as broad; pedicel longer than F1; F1–3 each slightly longer than broad, F4 quadrate; clava shorter than funicle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136C9FFC1FF9CFF68FE601CE477CD" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,753]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">
Mesosoma with pronotum triangular, nearly as long as mesoscutum, and 2× as broad as long; mesoscutum 2× as broad as long; scutellum 1.35× as broad as long; pronotum with slightly raised, irregular reticulations; mesoscutum with shallow reticulations; scutellum with raised reticulations, the cells very small, with sides and apex smooth [Scutellum with the sub-apical pair of long, scale-like setae lost.]; setae sparse, silvery white. Fore wing 2.75× as long as broad; width of ray II broader than width of hyaline window between ray II and ray III; rays III and IV not distinctly separated by a hyaline window, but appear as a single large apical infuscation; ray V as broad as ray II (
<figureCitation id="13552A4CFFC1FF9CFF0FFD481CF377CD" box="[160,229,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 1, 2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1412,1436]" captionTargetBox="[156,1413,790,1374]" captionTargetId="figure-297@4.[156,1431,774,1385]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1, 2. Caenohomalopoda albifuniculata Hayat, holotype, female. 1, antenna; 2, fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524430" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524430/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF116641FFC1FF9CFF38FA1B188270A0" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6524430" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6524430" box="[151,1172,1412,1436]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6524430/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" startId="4.[151,264,1412,1436]" targetBox="[156,1413,790,1374]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BD136C9FFC1FF9CFF38FA1B188270A0" blockId="4.[151,1172,1412,1436]" box="[151,1172,1412,1436]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">
<emphasis id="B91AEADBFFC1FF9CFF38FA1B1D2C70A0" bold="true" box="[151,314,1412,1436]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">FIGURES 1, 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D4AFFC1FF9CFEEEFA1B1ECD70A0" authority="Hayat" authorityName="Hayat" box="[321,731,1412,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Caenohomalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albifuniculata">
<emphasis id="B91AEADBFFC1FF9CFEEEFA1B1E8070A0" box="[321,662,1412,1436]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Caenohomalopoda albifuniculata</emphasis>
Hayat
</taxonomicName>
, holotype, female. 1, antenna; 2, fore wing.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD136C9FFC1FF9CFF68FA54185D7334" blockId="4.[151,1437,1482,1904]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Metasoma 1.76× as long as mesosoma and 1.3× as long as head and mesosoma combined; TVII elongate, pointed apically; exserted part of ovipositor about one-seventh gaster length (13:90).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136C9FFC1FF9CFF68F98D1D937310" blockId="4.[151,1437,1482,1904]" box="[199,389,1554,1581]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">
<emphasis id="B91AEADBFFC1FF9CFF68F98D1D177310" box="[199,257,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
