<subSubSection id="C3746542FFC1FF9CFF68F9591E03724C" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD136C9FFC1FF9CFF68F9591E03724C" blockId="4.[151,1437,1482,1904]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">
<emphasis id="B91AEADBFFC1FF9CFF68F9591D5973DC" bold="true" box="[199,335,1734,1760]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">Comments.</emphasis>
The above redescription is largely based on the original description and figures given by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B38FFC1FF9CFA93F9581D967238" author="Hayat, M. &amp; Veenakumari, K." pageId="4" pageNumber="251" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref13658" refString="Hayat, M. &amp; Veenakumari, K. (2014) Records and descriptions of Encyrtidae (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea) from southern India - 1. Journal of Insect Systematics, 1 (1), 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2014">Hayat &amp; Veenakumari (2014)</bibRefCitation>
, and study of the slide-mounted antenna and fore wing of the 
<typeStatus id="54D5886BFFC1FF9CFB93F97518B47238" box="[1084,1186,1770,1796]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">holotype</typeStatus>
. The only character in which this species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D4AFFC1FF9CFE5AF8901F6A7215" authority="(Tachikawa, 1956)" baseAuthorityName="Tachikawa" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[501,892,1806,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Pseudhomalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shikokuensis">
<emphasis id="B91AEADBFFC1FF9CFE5AF8901EB27214" box="[501,676,1806,1833]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">C. shikokuensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B38FFC1FF9CFD1DF8911F627215" author="Tachikawa, T." box="[690,884,1806,1833]" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" pagination="90 - 96" refId="ref14132" refString="Tachikawa, T. (1956) Description of a new species of the genus Pseudhomalopoda Girault from Japan, with a list of the known species and their hosts of the Habrolepis- like genera (Hymenoptera: Encyrtidae). Insecta Matsumurana, 20 (3 - 4), 90 - 96." type="journal article" year="1956">Tachikawa, 1956</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D4AFFC1FF9CFC1CF89018347214" authorityName="Fatima &amp; Zeya" authorityYear="2022" box="[947,1058,1806,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Caenohomalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sudhiri">
<emphasis id="B91AEADBFFC1FF9CFC1CF89018347214" box="[947,1058,1806,1833]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">C. sudhiri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is in having the fore wing clearly less than 3× as long as broad and apically broadly rounded. Otherwise, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D4AFFC1FF9CFC11F8AC186A7270" box="[958,1148,1842,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Encyrtidae" genus="Caenohomalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="251" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albifuniculata">
<emphasis id="B91AEADBFFC1FF9CFC11F8AC186A7270" box="[958,1148,1842,1869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="251">C. albifuniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from both species by the characters given in the key.
</paragraph>
